    {\displaystyle x_{0},\dots ,\ x_{n}}
   are distinct, then V is a square matrix with non-zero determinant, i.e. an invertible matrix. Thus, given V and y, one can find the required 
  
    
      
        p
        (
        x
        )
      
    
    {\displaystyle p(x)}
   by solving for its coefficients 
  
    
      
