    {\displaystyle f(x)=(x-x_{0})\cdots (x-x_{n})}
  . This is easily demonstrated: the polynomials clearly satisfy 
  
    
      
        
          L
          
            j
          
        
        (
        
          x
          
            i
          
        
        )
        =
        0
      
    
    {\displaystyle L_{j}(x_{i})=0}
   for 
  
    
      
        i
        ≠
        j
      
    
    {\displaystyle i\neq j}
   while 
  
    
      
        
          L
          
            j
          
        
        (
        
